review_blob:
Nice and spicy with a little funk, almost like they could pull this off as a jalapeno saison, in a good way. Nice picnic beer. Reminder... you do get little heat on this one.
Nice brew.

Bottle, enjoy by 03/04/14.
Well, my first try of the NEW Ruination.
Being a long time fan of this brew I had to seek this one out fresh. Stone increased the malt bill to bring this up to 8.2% from 7.7% apv and subtlety changed the bittering hops. This IS still a hop bomb for sure. Same minimal white head and great lacing. The aroma is big citrus and a little piney. Taste is bitter grapefruit and lemon zest with a little pine and a nice smooth malty sweetness that, tastes way better balanced to me.
And just when you thought it was over, the hops come back with a vengeance.
A true ride for the tastebuds! Well tweaked Stone!

Hazy burnt orange hue with decent off white frothy head (for a gentle pour at that) and very nice lacing.
Aroma, a huge orange citrus and some fresh cut grass.
Taste is citrusy orange / grapefruit with a finish of resinous hops.
The mouthfeel is silky and finishes with a nice bitter hoppiness bite. Wonderful IPA. Definitely on my buy again list.
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob:
Smell is almost port wine malty oak.
Almost no head that quickly falls to nothing and relatively no lacing.
Now the taste is really intriguing, with lots of sweet rye malt with a little of the port and oak. Moderate carbonation with some warmth and a bit of alcohol through the nose.
The feel is smooth and a little prickly from the carbonation....very nice as it warms.
Overall a very good cold evening brew.
Nice.

Well, I had to do this side by side w/Pumking.....I have to say I always thought Pumking was too sweet for my tastes (not for my better half) and now ST has gotten me on this one. 
I always loved pumpkin pie and coffee together. This ale really hits the mark.
Aroma... Nutmeg, cinnamon, just like the pie
Appearance...Opaque black (if there is such a thing). Nice fluffy caramel colored head with decent lacing.
Taste...This is what I always thought Pumking should taste like. Rich, sweet, bready/crust, and the coffee finish that I crave from a pumpkin ale. Very similar spices to Pumking.
Palate...Pretty smooth but, Id prefer a little less carbonation to balance it out.
Overall...I think they nailed it on this one....almost perfect. Now to find a case.

Smell a little sour w/herbal undertones...(year old+/-) appearance is somewhat cloudy.... But the palate really shines. Very nice mouth feel and the herbs are still there in small amounts. Sweet herbs, like a very good accoupliment to a lamb dish or cheese plate. Well put together..... Even after a year old. Do it again....Stone DFH V......
beer_name: Dogfish Head / Victory / Stone Saison du BUFF

review_blob: Poured a nice clear burnt orange,small 1/2 finger head, decent lacing. This is one of, if not the best, DIPA Ive ever had ! The aroma hits you right in the face HOPS..HOPS.. HOPS. Nice citrusy/resinous aroma. The taste is a balanced bitter/sweet and lingers forever. I dont know if this could be bettered in any way. This is the way I remembered it from last year, smooth on the palate and delicious. Dont wait to try this fresh, as it does not age well.
